<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1087] Empty topic list causes consumer to fetch metadata of all topics</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1087</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ClientUtils fetches metadata for all topics if the topic set is empty. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the topic list of a consumer is empty, the following happens if a rebalance is triggered:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The fetcher is restarted, fetcher.startConnections() starts a LeaderFinderThread&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;LeaderFinderThread waits on a condition&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fetcher.startConnections() signals the aforementioned condition&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;LeaderFinderThread obtains metadata for all topics since the topic list is empty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
